<HEADLINE>
<P>
'COOL' ACCENT MARKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Monsieur Jacques Toubon (All Good), the defender of the French language 
(Opinion, July 10) would turn into Toutmechant (All Mean) if he saw the 
violence you do to his language. Decontracte (meaning relaxed) as ersatz for 
English "cool" is meaningless without two accents, especially the last one. As 
a multicultural paper, isn't it time that you use an accent aigu , accent 
grave, circumflex, as well as an umlaut, a tilde and other foreign symbols? 
</P>
<P>
 P.S. Decontract e ain't in no way cool. 
</P>
<P>
 G. BORDING MATHIEU 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
