<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: CRAYON FIRM SMELLS MONEY IN NEW IDEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crayola crayons, one of the most familiar smells of childhood, are about to 
throw the younger generation for a fruit loop. 
</P>
<P>
 Binney & Smith Co. is introducing 16 crayons containing miniature capsules 
that burst with aroma as they are used. The scents include cherries, chocolate, 
licorice, bananas and bubble gum. "This idea smelled like a winner from day one 
because it brought a whole new dimension to the coloring experience," spokesman 
Brad Drexler said. 
</P>
<P>
 Binney & Smith turned up its nose at some scents, including blue cheese, 
leather, new car, peanut butter and skunk. 
</P>
