<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Arts Council has raised the grant rankings of two Orange County 
music organizations. The Pacific Chorale went from a 4- last year to a 4 on the 
CAC's 1 to 4 scale, while the Pacific Symphony moved from a 3+to a 4-.They have 
requested $39,632 and $221,283, respectively, in state arts support this year. 
The council's rankings of two other groups were unchanged from last year: 
Master Chorale of Orange County, 3- (requesting $39,000); and Opera Pacific, 
4-($221,283). Rankings are used to determine grant amounts, which the council 
will announce at its Sept. 8 meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor Art Museum is seeking volunteer tour guides. The museum offers 
a September-through-May training program that focuses on contemporary art 
history, public speaking and touring techniques. Bilingual applicants are 
particularly needed. For further information, or to schedule an interview, call 
the Newport Harbor education department: (714) 759-1122. 
</P>
