<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: SANTIAGO; A CHOICE IN CHILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chile's Christian Democrats, the leading force in the governing coalition, 
will elect a new party chairman Saturday.Alejandro Foxley, finance minister 
until last March, is the top candidate. 
</P>
<P>
 The party chairmanship is a potential steppingstone toward the Chilean 
presidency, and Foxley is known to have presidential ambitions. President 
Eduardo Frei, who took office in March, was chairman of the party before he 
launched his winning campaign last year. 
</P>
