<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT'S THE DEAL: BODY WATCH; HOW TO BECOME A FORMER SMOKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN DOHENY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Every day, another part of the planet is declared off-limits for puffing, or 
so it seems to smokers.So, how to quit? Some options and their costs: 
</P>
<P>
 * Acupuncture, one-hour session, $30 (number of sessions required depends on 
length and severity of habit). 
</P>
<P>
 * Nicorette gum, by prescription, 96-pack, $48. 
</P>
<P>
 * Hypnosis, one-hour session, $100 to $150. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nicoderm patches, by prescription, 10-week supply in three strengths, $610. 
KATHLEEN DOHENY 
</P>
</TEXT>
