<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTH: FULLERTON; MUSEUM IS SEEKING TRUSTEE CANDIDATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fullerton Museum Center is seeking candidates to apply for four seats on 
its board of trustees. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants do not have to be Fullerton residents but must be interested in 
playing an active role in fund raising and programming, museum officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 21-member board raises money to help finance exhibitions and provides 
staff with recommendations regarding programs. It is a nonprofit organization 
that works with the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at the museum, 301 N. Pomona Ave., and must be 
returned by 4 p.m. Sunday. A nominations committee will then conduct interviews 
and choose the new trustees. MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
