<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: DOWNEY; PSYCHIATRIST 
RECOMMENDS NO PAROLE FOR MOLESTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A psychiatrist has recommended that convicted child molester Joe Caro Jr., who 
was due for parole last Saturday, be sent back to prison for another year. 
</P>
<P>
 Caro's record of sex crimes against children dates to 1952. His scheduled 
release caused an uproar last week in Downey, where the state Department of 
Corrections had arranged for the 74-year-old man to move into a motel next door 
to a preschool playground. 
</P>
<P>
 Parole officials reconsidered Caro's placement after receiving hundreds of 
phone calls. A hearing on his parole has been set for next month, when his 
psychiatric evaluation will be reviewed. 
</P>
