<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Biotech leader Genentech Inc. said surging sales helped its second-quarter 
earnings more than triple compared to a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Profit for the quarter ended June 30 increased to $33.4 million, or 28 cents a 
share, from $10.4 million, or 9 cents a share, in the second quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue increased 15% to $194.9 million from $169.8 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The profit surge was fueled in part by increased demand for the drug t-PA. 
Quarterly sales of the clot-dissolving drug, also known as Activase, increased 
32% to $73.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
