<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coca-Cola Co. reported that worldwide marketing initiatives, new ad campaigns 
and the reintroduction of the contour Coke bottle helped boost second-quarter 
profit by 12%. 
</P>
<P>
 For the three months ended June 30, the Atlanta-based company earned $758 
million, or 59 cents a share, compared to $678 million, or 52 cents a share, in 
the same period a year ago. Revenue rose 11% to $4.34 billion, from $3.9 
billion. 
</P>
