ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: STOCK BROKERAGE, 2 PRINCIPALS FINED AND EXPELLED BY NASD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Costa Mesa stock brokerage, Unex Capital Corp., and two of its principals 
have been expelled from the securities industry, the National Assn. of 
Securities Dealers said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Unex principal Lawrence Robert Hazlewood was fined $50,000 and barred from 
associating with any NASD member, while Mona Lynn Houseworth, also a principal, 
was fined $15,000. The company itself was fined $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The association said the actions were taken because Houseworth allowed 
Hazlewood to act as a principal and help run Unex though Hazlewood had never 
passed the qualifying test to become a principal and never registered with NASD 
as a principal. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither Hazlewood nor Houseworth could be reached for comment. 
