REGIONAL EARNINGS: INTERLINK ELECTRONICS REPORTS QUARTERLY LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Interlink Electronics , a Camarillo-based producer of cursor control devices 
for computers, reported a net loss of $359,000 for the second quarter ended 
June 30, compared to a net loss of $945,000 for the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue for the recent quarter increased 56% to $1.9 million from $1.21 
million for the same three-month period of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months ended June 30, the company reported a net loss of $953,000 
on revenue of $3.25 million, compared to a $1.89 million loss on revenue of 
$2.28 million for the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 E. Michael Thoben, chief executive of Interlink, attributed part of the 
revenue growth to shipments of a newly introduced remote pointing device for 
bundling with IBM notebook computers. 
