<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: VITESSE SEMICONDUCTOR REPORTS SLIM PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vitesse Semiconductor Corp. of Camarillo reported a profit of $128,000 for the 
fiscal third quarter ended June 30, compared to a net loss of $4.2 million for 
the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The results represent the first profit in two years for the company, which 
manufactures gallium-arsenide semiconductors for computing and other 
uses.Vitesse, which has struggled with the decline of the supercomputer market, 
attributed the profit to growth in the company's communications business -- new 
customers include AT & T and Intel Corp. -- and recent cost-reduction measures. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue in the third quarter totaled $9.2 million, a 31% increase over the $7 
million in the year-ago quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite the return to profitability, the company reported a net loss of $4.3 
million on revenue of $25.9 million for the first nine months of fiscal 1994. 
During the same period a year ago, the company reported a net loss of $15.9 
million on revenue of $18.4 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
