<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ON ASSIGNMENT'S REVENUE, PROFIT HIKE IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Assignment Inc., a Calabasas provider of temporary laboratory personnel, 
reported gains in its second-quarter profit and revenue, which it said 
reflected a record number of employees on temporary assignment and increased 
productivity. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's net income in the quarter ended June 30 was $894,000, a 37% 
increase from $610,000 in earnings a year earlier. Its quarterly revenue rose 
29%, to $12.3 million from $9.59 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, On Assignment earnings grew 31% to $1.47 million, while 
revenue was up 23%, to $22.7 million. In the first half of 1993, it earned 
$1.13 million on $18.5 million in revenue. 
</P>
