<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: LTC PROPERTIES NET INCOME DOUBLES TO $3.83 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LTC Properties Inc., an Oxnard real estate investment trust that invests in 
long-term care and other health-care facilities, reported a doubling of its net 
income in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 LTC earned $3.83 million in the three months that ended June 30, compared to a 
$1.88-million profit a year before. Its revenue rose 53%, to $6.31 million from 
$4.12 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The trust's net income more than doubled in the recent six-month period, to 
$6.28 million, while its revenue climbed 58%, to $11.9 million. A year earlier, 
it earned $3 million on $7.49 million in revenue. 
</P>
