<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: AMGEN REPORTS NET INCOME OF $107.5 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amgen Inc., a Thousand Oaks-based biotechnology company, reported net income 
of $107.5 million for the second quarter ended June 30, a 7% rise from the 
$100.2 million in profit the company reported for the same quarter a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue in the recent quarter rose 21% to $415 million from the $343 million 
in revenue the company reported for the second quarter last year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months ended June 30, Amgen reported net income of $200.9 million 
on revenue of $779 million, compared to the $189.5-million profit the company 
earned on revenue of $653 million for the first six months of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed much of the recent growth to the continued success of 
its two blood cell-producing drugs, Epogen and Neupogen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071994-0169 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 062090 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
