<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: WEST COAST DISPLAYS TAPPED TO DO EXHIBIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 West Coast Displays, based in Ventura, has been chosen to design and build a 
major trade-show exhibit for Gibbs & Associates, a Moorpark firm that produces 
software for automated factory systems. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob Hartz, West Coast's president, says the project will be his company's 
first since the recent acquisition of a graphics firm. He said its expertise 
will be used in producing a 20- by 30-foot exhibit that will be used by Gibbs 
during a Chicago event in September. 
</P>
<P>
 Other clients of privately held West Coast Displays have included Hughes 
Aircraft, Memorex, Power-One, Rockwell International and Teledyne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
