<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / CENTRAL: TUSTIN; CHAMBER HONORS 2 COMMUNITY ACTIVISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An attorney and a restaurateur have been named Tustin's Man and Woman of the 
Year for their community involvement. The awards were presented at the Tustin 
Chamber of Commerce's 37th annual officers installation dinner. 
</P>
<P>
 Man of the Year Vic Gorham, who also was installed as chamber president for 
1994-95, is a local attorney who specializes in estate planning and business 
law. He is a former president of the Tustin Host Lions Club and immediate past 
president of the Boys and Girls Club of Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
 Gorham also is a founding director of the North Tustin Community Assn. and has 
been active with the city's chili cook-off steering committee for the past 
three years. 
</P>
<P>
 Woman of the Year Angie Kardashian owns Angie's Cuisine Italiano in Tustin. 
She is a former chamber president and current chamber liaison to the Marine 
Corps Air Station in Tustin. Her volunteer efforts include hosting a free 
Thanksgiving dinner at her restaurant for Marine service personnel and their 
families. 
</P>
<P>
 Kardashian also was contestant coordinator of the Miss Tustin Scholarship 
Pageant for five years and helps support scholarship funds at Tustin High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 Presenting the awards were last year's Man and Woman of the Year, David Nisson 
and Judy Houlihan. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
