<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / CENTRAL: SANTA ANA; PUBLIC HAS ROLE IN HIRING SCHOOLS 
CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Ana Unified School District officials are seeking help from the public 
to find out what qualities, attributes and experience the district's new 
superintendent should have, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Community members who wish to respond may attend special meetings on Thursday, 
call the district with comments or request a questionnaire, district 
spokeswoman Diane Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 People who want to meet with the district's search consultant, Richard 
Montgomery, should call the district at (714) 558-5515 to schedule an 
appointment for Thursday. People may use the same phone number to request a 
survey. 
</P>
<P>
 Mailed comments may be sent to Montgomery at district headquarters, 1405 
French St., Santa Ana, Calif. 92701. 
</P>
<P>
 The search is expected to take about four months, with potential candidates 
being interviewed about mid-October and a new superintendent being chosen by 
the end of October, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Board of Education will fill the vacancy left by Rudy Castruita, who left 
the district Friday after nine years of service. He is leaving to become the 
San Diego County superintendent of schools.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
