<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / COSTA MESA / NEWPORT / IRVINE: NEWPORT BEACH; COUNCILMAN 
ELECTED SANITATION CHAIRMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Councilman John C. Cox Jr. has been elected to serve a one-year term as 
chairman of the Orange County Sanitation District. 
</P>
<P>
 Cox has represented Newport Beach on the district's board of directors for the 
past 14 years, where he has served as vice chairman and chairman of the 
Conservation, Reclamation and Reuse Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Peer Swan, chairman of the Irvine Ranch Water District, was nominated to serve 
as vice chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 The nine sanitation districts provide waste water management services for more 
than 2 million residents and businesses in northwest Orange County. BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
