<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / COUNTYWIDE: ELECTION LINEUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The filing period opened Monday for city council, school district and special 
district candidates in the Nov. 8 general election. Candidacy papers must be 
filed by Aug. 12.City council elections will be held in 28 of Orange County's 
31 cities (Dana Point, Seal Beach and Tustin held council elections earlier 
this year). There will also be elections in four community college districts, 
three high school districts, 10 unified school districts and 13 elementary 
school districts. Special district elections will be held for directors and 
trustees of community services, water, sanitary, irrigation, parks and 
recreation, and library districts. Cities holding council and mayoral elections 
in November: 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim: mayor, two council 
</P>
<P>
 Brea: three council 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park: three council 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa: two council 
</P>
<P>
