<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN STABBED IN SPAT OVER CAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An argument over a pet cat landed one man in the hospital with a stab wound 
and another in jail Monday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police and neighbors, the argument began when James E. Odell's 
cat got under a neighbor's car in the mobile home park where the two live in 
the 14000 block of Hoover Street. 
</P>
<P>
 During the fight, according to Sgt. Tom Pixler of the Westminster Police 
Department, a neighbor, Gerard Whalen, stabbed Odell with a pocketknife. 
</P>
<P>
 Whalen, 37, was arrested and taken to the Orange County Jail where he was 
booked on suspicion of attempted murder, Pixler said. 
</P>
<P>
 Odell, 28, was in stable condition at UCI Medical Center with a knife wound in 
the abdomen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071994-0194 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 062115 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
July 19, 1994, Tuesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
