<P>
WOMAN CROSSING STREET KILLED BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 69-year-old woman died Monday after being hit by a car on the 3400 block of 
West Ball Road.Anna Stearns of Anaheim was taken to Anaheim General Hospital, 
where she was pronounced dead on arrival. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, Stearns was crossing the street when she was struck by a 
blue 1983 Ford driven by Barbara Annette Grefsrud, 54, of Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 A police spokesman said the cause of the accident was still under 
investigation. 
</P>
