<P>
183 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SHERMAN OAKS; COUNCIL PROPOSES LOCAL NEWSPAPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sherman Oaks Town Council has discussed ways to encourage the 
establishment of a community newspaper with a strong focus on local news. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a gap that's missing," Nancy Schmidt, president of the Sherman Oaks 
Chamber of Commerce, said last week."It provides a way for the women's club to 
talk about what they're doing, or for the YMCA to talk about what they're 
doing." 
</P>
<P>
 Two options for nurturing a newspaper were discussed by the Town Council last 
week. One option would be for one of the council's member-entities to contract 
with a newsletter company, which would publish the newspaper. The other is to 
support an independent newspaper publisher's establishment of a newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
 Hall Media Group -- which publishes the Santa Monica News, Brentwood News and 
Westwood News -- is said to be considering the Sherman Oaks-Studio City area 
for a possible fourth edition. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Publisher Jeff Hall said) he is investigating this area," said Schmidt. "His 
company is determining whether there is enough financial support -- in other 
words, advertising -- to develop a paper." KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
