<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PANORAMA CITY; KATZ TO HOST STATE GOVERNMENT DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Assemblyman Richard Katz (D-Sylmar) will host the 14th annual State Government 
Day at Panorama Mall Saturday, where residents will be encouraged to find out 
how local and state government organizations can serve them. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will feature exhibits from nearly 40 government agencies and 
organizations.The agency representatives will also take suggestions, complaints 
and questions from the public. 
</P>
<P>
 Agencies expected to set up exhibits include the California Highway Patrol, 
the California Museum of Science and Industry, the Employment Development 
Department and the Los Angeles City Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Department of Water and Power will display the GM Impact EV 
electric car, which has a city driving range of 70 miles per charge and a top 
speed of 80 m.p.h. The car is part of a joint project with the Southern 
California Edison Co. and General Motors to field-test the vehicle for its 
practicality. 
</P>
<P>
 There will also be displays by Cal State Northridge, the Department of Social 
Services and the Valley Community Clinic. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will take place from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the mall, located at 8401 
Van Nuys Blvd. ED BOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
