</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old girl who was the subject of a massive police search was found by 
security guard Monday in a Van Nuys neighborhood, accompanied by a man whom 
police later arrested on suspicion of rape, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who police said has the mental capacity of a 7-year-old, was found 
about 4:30 p.m. in the 15000 block of Oxnard Avenue by a private security guard 
who saw her walking in an alley with an adult man, said Officer Don Cox of the 
Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Guillermo Perez Ayon, 37, a transient, was being held in lieu of $50,000 bail 
on suspicion of rape of an incompetent person, Cox said. 
</P>
<P>
 The guard recognized the girl from photographs that had been run on television 
and distributed on 1,300 leaflets along Ventura Boulevard, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 She had walked away from her home in Woodland Hills on Sunday afternoon, 
authorities said. She was last seen Sunday by a store clerk at a bus bench at 
the corner of Corbin Street and Ventura Boulevard between 5 p.m. and 5:30 p.m., 
said Detective Bud Mehringer, juvenile coordinator at the West Valley Division. 
</P>
<P>
 Her disappearance prompted an intense search that began Sunday when 
authorities sent rescue teams equipped with search and tracking dogs into the 
hillside area above her home. 
