<P>
CASTAIC PRISON ESCAPEE REMAINS AT LARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Van Nuys man convicted of driving under the influence remains at large after 
apparently scaling a prison fence that had been topped with razor wire. 
</P>
<P>
 Max Arroyo, 27, was discovered missing from the Peter J. Pitchess Honor Rancho 
facility at 5:50 Sunday morning during a routine inmate count, according to 
Deputy Gabe Ramirez. Arroyo was last accounted for during a similar check at 3 
a.m. 
</P>
