Flynn lost to Weis in the race for superintendent. 
</P>
<P>
 As principal of the county's three schools for juvenile offenders, Flynn was 
employed by the county schools office. Weis was his boss. 
</P>
<P>
 Weis said at the time the firing was based solely on Flynn's job performance, 
not on Flynn's campaign against his supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 But Flynn's attorney and some of his supporters have challenged the firing 
arguing that only the board, not the superintendent, has the right to make such 
personnel decisions. MAIA DAVIS 
