EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CONEJO VALLEY; SCHOOL BOARD SEAT OPEN UNTIL ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The now vacant seat of a retired Conejo Valley Unified School District Board 
member will remain open until the November general election, district officials 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 A member of the school board for nearly nine years, William Henry Jr. resigned 
July 1 after moving to Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 At the time of his announcement, district officials were uncertain whether to 
hold a special election, appoint a replacement or leave the seat empty. The 
seat is up for election this fall. 
</P>
<P>
 But Ventura County election officials Monday told Supt. Jerry Gross that 
according to the state education code, the district can simply leave Henry's 
seat open until the next general election. 
</P>
<P>
 "The board doesn't have to take a vote on this," Gross said. 
</P>
<P>
 Trustee Dorothy Beaubien agreed that the seat should remain open. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think we'll fill it, because the election is so close," she said. "We 
all sort of had the same feeling that it would be foolish." 
</P>
<P>
 Three seats for the Conejo Valley school board are up for reelection in the 
fall: Henry's and those held by trustees Mildred Lynch and Richard Newman. 
TRACY WILSON 
