<HEADLINE>
<P>
POSITIVE STORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your article about our Catholic "surfing priest" on July 10 was wonderfully 
refreshing to read. 
</P>
<P>
 However, a fine article was tainted by the four paragraphs devoted to the past 
incident of Father David Piroli. 
</P>
<P>
 So often the media assumes the public desires to hear about the scandalous and 
criminal actions of the clergy. I assure you that is false. It was very 
pleasing to read a positive and well-written article on a healthy, happy 
priest, Father Dennis Mongrain, who is dedicated to building up the body of 
Christ as well as his own biceps. 
</P>
<P>
 MARYANN TENNANT, Newbury Park 
