<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOCUS ON ENTERTAINMENT STOCKS: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Market trends: Microsoft Corp. was the volume leader in Monday's trading. 
Elsewhere, Home Shopping Network Inc., which operates a retail shopping channel 
on cable television, announced a second-quarter profit of $1.9 million on sales 
of $274.0 million, compared to a year-ago profit of $1.6 million on sales of 
$250.3 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
